title: VEGOILS-Market factors to watch Oct 5
text:
The following factors are likely to influence Malaysian palm oil futures and other vegetable oil 
markets. 
FUNDAMENTALS 
* Malaysian palm oil futures fell on Friday after hitting a 15-month high earlier in the week as 
buyers started looking at alternatives such as soybean oil. 
* U.S. wheat futures sank on Friday on a round of end-of-week profit taking after prices hit an 
8-1/2 week high on Thursday, traders said. 
* Crude prices erased early losses to rise by 1 percent or more on Friday after a report showing 
the fifth weekly decline in the U.S. oil rig count renewed the debate over falling production in 
the world's top oil consumer. 
MARKET NEWS 
* Bond prices climbed on Friday after a weak U.S. employment report increased worry about 
slowing global growth, while global equities were able to rebound from an initial selloff to 
close with strong gains. 
> Glencore in talks on agriculture assets -sources 
> Cocoa traders worried after I.Coast omits Sucden from exporters 
> Ghana expects cocoa output rebound as new season starts 
> India's sugar export boost plan looks flawed-traders 
> Milder weather may limit EU maize losses as harvest gets going 
DATA/EVENTS 
> Cargo surveyor ITS releases Malaysia's May 1-10 palm oil export data on October 10. 
> Cargo surveyor Societe Generale de Surveillance unveils August 1-10 palm oil exports in 
Malaysia on October 10.
